{
  "texts": [
    "Offline Preference Learning Stage In the second phase, the SFT model π SFT is trained offline with a collection of human preference data.",
    "This is often done using DPO, which first re-parametrizes the reward r in terms of the optimal policy 1:",
    "where π ref is a reference policy, β controls the strength of the KL-divergence, and Z(x) is the partition function.",
    "Then, DPO optimizes the following objective treating the LMs as reward models:",
    "1 Under the formulation of reward maximization under a KL-divergence constraint where (x, y w, y l) are preference pairs consisting of the prompt, the winning response, and the losing response, respectively; and r w = r(x w, y w), r l = r(x l, y l) are rewards given a choice of π θ and π ref."
  ]
}